This joint is cheap and affordable as I mostly prefer takeaways from here. 
Had gulab jamun, chicken chowmein, chili chicken and paneer masala recently. 
Except the chill chicken and gulab jamun, the rest items were okayish. The chili chicken was good but the curry leaves in it was a total mess. 
The gulab jamun was amazing. 
The staff here is polite and very attentive. If you are looking for a paisa-wasool yet tasty food experience, then definitely you can try this place.
All in all, it was a nice experience for me.thegreedygluttonsgastronomicjourney.wordpress.com
Hygiene is not a very strong thing in this place. But the food is dirt cheap. And also tasty. You can get garma garm rotis, rice thalis at fifty bucks , paneer curries and lots more.

I generally have the chicken Manchurian, chili chicken, chicken 65 and chicken masala here.. Tastes of food is good and quantity is also good..
Biriyani here is also good. Small food point so i basically take away the food...

A small canteen which serves decent quality food at cheap bucks.. 
I generally have the gobi manchurian, chili chicken, chicken 65 and chicken masala here.. Tastes quite good, given the price charged.. 
Biriyani here is also good, but its dry..  
Generally i do take aways from here...
This eatery is for those who look out for pucca home style north Indian curries n hot pulkas /paranthas. One can try paneer butter masala, egg bhurji or chicken masala here.
